From 28ccb5e5f6cf40fbd286f55e2512dc9f91944adf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: radhevrishi <radhev.232@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 26 May 2026 11:33:53 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] patch 0890: vercel.json - exclude Next.js native routes from
 Render proxy

THE ACTUAL ROOT CAUSE of why BLISSGVS / MARKSANS / BIRLAPREC / AVROIND
kept showing "thin-float expansion" despite patches 0886-0889 fixing
every other layer of the pipeline.

Diagnostic: curl https://market-cockpit.vercel.app/api/v1/news-india/BLISSGVS
returns {"detail":"Not Found"} - FastAPI format, not Next.js. Response
header x-render-origin-server=uvicorn confirms the request is being
served by the Render Python backend, NOT by my Next.js route at
src/app/api/v1/news-india/[ticker]/route.ts.

The previous vercel.json had a single catch-all rewrite:
  { source: "/api/v1/:path*",
    destination: "https://market-cockpit-api.onrender.com/api/v1/:path*" }

That forwarded EVERY /api/v1/* request to Render, even when a Next.js
route file existed. The Render backend does not have /api/v1/news-india,
so the request 404ed. The home page Movers enrichment got an empty
news payload, the engine had no catalyst, the row fell through to the
LIQUIDITY_VACUUM fallback - the "thin-float expansion" the user kept
seeing.

The next.config.js comment even explicitly said
  "On Vercel, Next.js API routes serve /api/v1/* natively. No rewrite
   needed."
- but vercel.json contradicted it. The contradiction never got noticed
because most of the Next.js routes that have been added (graded,
concall-intel/live-feed, etc) HAPPEN to have matching Render endpoints,
so the proxy returned the same data and looked "fine". news-india
never had a Render counterpart - the bug only surfaced for that path.

Fix: passthrough self-rewrites for every Next.js-native namespace
BEFORE the Render catch-all. Vercel evaluates rewrites top-to-bottom;
a self-rewrite (source == destination) tells the edge "do nothing,
let Next.js handle this natively". The final catch-all stays so any
genuinely Render-only endpoint still proxies correctly.

Namespaces excluded from Render proxy:
  news-india, news, concall-intel, concall, earnings, heartbeat,
  edgar, order-book, rating-actions, super-investor-flow,
  super-investor-news, alerts, cron, breadth, admin, themes,
  specsit, special-situations, ticker-roles, transmission, public,
  source-tier, system-status

Did NOT include the _comment field (CLAUDE.md S18.5 P0706 lesson:
Vercel rejects vercel.json with non-schema fields).
---
 frontend/vercel.json | 96 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 96 insertions(+)

diff --git a/frontend/vercel.json b/frontend/vercel.json
index b4d3001..0fc3ee1 100644
--- a/frontend/vercel.json
+++ b/frontend/vercel.json
@@ -1,5 +1,101 @@
 {
   "rewrites": [
+    {
+      "source": "/api/v1/news-india/:path*",
+      "destination": "/api/v1/news-india/:path*"
+    },
+    {
